                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic"/>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">fols. 5ra-237vc (apart from the fols. written in hand b), 250ra-302vc, 316ra-329ra: the letters are slender, tall and upright (occasionally right-sloping e.g., fol. 253vbc), but they are written inconsistently in a variety of ways.  The script is uneven and irregular throughout the Ms. It is usually neat and careful at the beginning of the quire and then gradually deteriorates. On fol. 22vb the letters are executed with a thinner nib. On fols. 100ra-101rb the letters are slightly bigger and written with a broader pen nib.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">fols. 20rc-21rc, 23vc, 24rbc, 25rv, 27rbc, 28vab, 29vb-vc, 76rc-vb, 77va, 78ra, 78vbc, 79va-vb, 80ra, 84rv, 92va-95rc, 95vc-98rb: on numerous fols. the script is conspicuously right-sloping.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">fols. 238ra-249vc, 304ra-315vc: the letters are short and wide, broadly spaced and slightly right-sloping. On fol. 315v the scribe used a compressed script to accommodate 66 lines of text within 39 ruled lines.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
